  "text": "The Firefox SpiderMonkey JIT compilation pipeline consists of the following key components:\n\n1. **IonCompile function** (js/src/jit/Ion.cpp, line 1765): This static function is the top-level entry point that orchestrates the Ion optimizing compiler. It creates the MIRGraph, CompileInfo, and MIRGenerator, then initiates both on-thread and off-thread compilation paths. It handles the creation of the WarpSnapshot and delegates to StartOffThreadIonCompile for background compilation.\n\n2. **IonCompileTask class** (js/src/jit/IonCompileTask.h:27, with implementation in IonCompileTask.cpp): This represents a single off-thread Ion compilation task. It inherits from both HelperThreadTask and mozilla::LinkedListElement<IonCompileTask>, containing a reference to MIRGenerator, a CodeGenerator pointer for the background-compiled code, and a WarpSnapshot. The runHelperThreadTask() method (line 23 in .cpp) is the entry point for off-thread execution.\n\n3. **BaselineScript class** (js/src/jit/BaselineJIT.h, line 189): This is the first-tier JIT compiler class representing baseline-compiled code. It stores method code pointers, warm-up check offsets, profiler instrumentation offsets, and a reference to any pending IonCompileTask (line 196). This is the baseline tier that provides fast startup before Ion compilation.\n\n4. **JitRuntime class** (js/src/jit/JitRuntime.h, line 121): This class manages per-runtime JIT state and infrastructure, including Ion compilation tasks, trampoline code, exception handlers, profiler frames, and various runtime JIT code pointers. It manages the ionLazyLinkList_ (line 224-225) which stores Ion compilation tasks waiting to get linked.\n\n5. **JitOptions configuration** (js/src/jit/JitOptions.h and JitOptions.cpp): The DefaultJitOptions struct (line 46 in header) defines all JIT configuration options including baselineJit, ion, osr, forceInlineCaches, and numerous optimization flags. A global instance JitOptions is created via MOZ_RUNINIT in JitOptions.cpp (line 22) to hold the actual runtime configuration.\n\nThese five components form the core of the SpiderMonkey JIT pipeline, with IonCompile orchestrating the overall flow, IonCompileTask handling off-thread work, BaselineScript providing the first tier, JitRuntime managing runtime state, and JitOptions controlling the compilation behavior."
}

